Bernard Madoff's massive fraud scheme spanned continents, ensnaring top investors who were oblivious to the con until his arrest.
The Ponzi scheme's unraveling shocked clients seeking withdrawals, revealing empty coffers.
The scandal implicated wealthy Americans and European banks, with losses potentially surpassing Lehman Brothers' collapse.
